Thomas Hobbes
1588-1679 (Westport, England)

• He was abandoned by his father at an early

age; was brought up by his uncle

• He studied at the University of Oxford at 15

years old

• Experienced the turbulent half of the

seventeenth century in England (conflict
between royalists and Parliamentarians)

• Sought refuge in France because of his

association with the royalist circles (he was
the tutor to Charles II of Wales) and his
antiparliamentarian writings

• Hobbes was a defender of an absolute

government

• He wrote the Leviathan (1651) before he

returned to England

https://www.biography.com/scholar/thomas-hobbes

Key Points

• Theory of human nature
• State of nature and laws of nature
• The social contract
• Sovereign power
• Types of government
• The right to resist

