Introduction

The purpose of this care plan is to provide a structured, compassionate, and personalized
approach to in-home care for Coral, an 88-year-old woman diagnosed with Alzheimer's
disease and incontinence issues. This plan emphasizes Coral's independence, dignity,
and overall well-being while addressing her specific needs and preferences. Given her
condition, the care plan is dynamic and will be regularly reviewed and updated to adapt to
any changes in Coral's health, preferences, and environment.
