INFO 2025-04-20 08:50:24,692 tasks 30 140287969074048 Context: ['Individualized Care & Engagement Plan for Karen\n\nThis care plan has been developed to ensure that Karen, receives the highest level of care\nand  support  while  allowing  her  to  continue  living  comfortably  at  home  with  her  beloved\ndog,  Casey.  As  her  cognitive  challenges  progresses  and  arthritis  affects  her  hand\ncoordination, this plan is designed to support her cognitive function, mobility, and personal\ncare while promoting independence and respecting her dignity.\n\nKaren’s care has transitioned from 8-hour shifts to live-in support at your request to provide\nmore  consistent  supervision  and  assistance.  To  further  enhance  nighttime  safety,  an\nassistive  device  bed  alarm  will  be  implemented  to  alert  caregivers  during  her  nighttime\nawakenings, ensuring immediate assistance and reducing fall risks.', 'Additionally, we strongly believe in promoting Karen’s independence and will not take over\ntasks that she can still manage herself. Instead, we will offer guidance and encouragement\nto help her maintain her sense of autonomy for as long as possible.\n\nThe following care plan outlines specific goals, care services, and engagement strategies\nto ensure Karen’s ongoing health and well-being. Regular reviews and communication will\nallow us to monitor her progress and make necessary adjustments as her needs evolve.\n\nThank you for your trust in creating this personalized plan for Karen. Please don’t hesitate\nto reach out if you have any questions.\n\n1. Ensure Safety and Comfort\n\nPrimary Goals\n\n•  Maintain a structured daily routine to minimize confusion and anxiety.\n•  Use an assistive device bed alarm to alert caregivers during nighttime awakenings,\n\nensuring prompt assistance and reducing fall risks.', 'in caring for Casey as much as possible.\n\n•  Maintain a safe home environment for both Karen and Casey.\n\n7. Maintain Effective Communication with Family and Healthcare Providers\n\n•  Share weekly updates with family members.\n•  Consult healthcare providers as needed to adjust care strategies.\n\n8. Review and Adapt the Care Plan as Needed\n\n•  Conduct monthly care reviews to assess Karen’s health and cognitive function.\n•  Modify the care plan as Karen’s needs evolve.\n\n\x0cPersonalized Engagement Program for Karen\n\nThis engagement plan is designed to support Karen’s cognitive function, emotional well-\nbeing, and independence while aligning with her interests and personality.\n\nActivities Tailored to Karen’s Interests\n\n1. Television & Storytelling\n\n•  TV viewing will be altered to remove soaps, which caused stress. Karen will now\nwatch lighter content like comedies, old musicals, animal-related shows, and\nfamily movies.', 'Dexterity exercises, music, Casey time\n\nAfternoon (2:00 - 4:00 PM) TV shows, reminiscence therapy, social engagement\n\nEvening (6:00 - 8:00 PM)\n\nLight conversation, reading, relaxation\n\nFinal Notes\n\nThis  integrated  care  and  engagement  plan  ensures  that  Karen  receives  consistent,\ncompassionate,  and  stimulating  care  while  maintaining  her  independence  and  dignity.\nAdjustments will be made as needed based on her evolving needs, preferences, and well-\nbeing.\n\nThank  you  for  your  involvement  in  Karen’s  care.  Please  feel  free  to  reach  out  with  any\nquestions or concerns.\n\n\x0cT I M E\n\nS U N D A Y\n\nM O N D A Y\n\nT U E S D A Y\n\nW E D N E S D A Y\n\nT H U R S D A Y\n\nF R I D A Y\n\nS A T U R D A Y\n\nM O R N I N G\n( 8 : 0 0   A M   -\n1 2 : 0 0   P M )\n\nWake-up &\nHygiene:\nBreakfast &\nhydration\nMobility\nexercises\n(stretching)\nSquish ball\nEngagement:\nReminiscence\ntherapy (photo\nviewing)']
