INFO 2025-04-21 06:55:52,263 documents 347 139778430064320 Chunks: [Document(id='doc_69_chunk_0', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_0', 'index': 0, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='Republic of the Philippines\nMINDANAO STATE UNIVERSITY\nMarawi City\n\nOFFICE OF THE SECRETARY OF THE UNIVERSITY\nAND OF THE BOARD OF REGENTS\n\nEXCERPTS FROM THE MINUTES OF THE 263RD MEETING OF THE BOARD OF REGENTS\nHELD  ON  JULY  7,  2023  AT  CHED  CONFERENCE  ROOM,  HEDC  BUILDING,  C.P.  GARCIA\nAVENUE, DILIMAN, QUEZON CITY\n======================================================================\n                     x-x-x\nx-x-x\n\n       x-x-x\n\n“RESOLUTION NO. 131, S. 2023”\n\nRESOLVED,  that  upon  the  recommendation  of  the  President  of  the\n\nUniversity and the Executive Committee of the Board of Regents, the proposal to\n\nconvert in the database History 003 (History of Filipino Muslims and Indigenous\n\nPeoples  of  MINSUPALA)  as  GEC  110,  Filipino  101  (Wika  at  Kultura  sa\n\nMapayapang  Lipunan)  as  GEC  120,  and  FILIPINO  102  (Ekokritisismo  at\n\nPagpapahalaga ng Kalikasan) as GEC 130, herein appended as Annex “F” and\n\nmade integral part of this resolution, is hereby APPROVED.'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_1', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_1', 'index': 1, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='Pagpapahalaga ng Kalikasan) as GEC 130, herein appended as Annex “F” and\n\nmade integral part of this resolution, is hereby APPROVED.\n\nx-x-x\n\n           x-x-x\n\n                     x-x-x\n\n           CERTIFIED TRUE AND CORRECT:\n\nAPPROVED”\n\nATTY. SHIDIK T. ABANTAS, MDM\n      Secretary of the University\n                                                                                      and of the Board of Regents\nSTA:rlf\n12 April 2024\n(Not valid without seal)\n\nUNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cResolution No. 131, S. 2023\n\nAnnex “F”\n\nDate; June 30, 2023\nProponent; Faculty of the History Department, College of Social Sciences and Humanities\n\nCourse Proposal\n\nRationale\n\nA.  Description of the Courses\n\nHIS003\n\nB. Expected Impact on Student\n\nC. Evaluation and Output of the course'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_2', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_2', 'index': 2, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='Course Proposal\n\nRationale\n\nA.  Description of the Courses\n\nHIS003\n\nB. Expected Impact on Student\n\nC. Evaluation and Output of the course\n\nThis course deals with a descriptive-analytical\nstudy of the history of the Muslims (Islamized\nnatives or Bangsamoro) and the Lumads from\nthe pre-Islamic period, Spanish colonial\nperiod, American occupation, Japanese\ninvasion, Philippine republic, Martial Law\ndown to the present. Particular emphasis on\nhow they fought against the forces of foreign\ncolonization and local domination which\nthreaten their way of life and their very\nexistence. Also, particular emphasis on the\ncatastrophic historical events that shaped the\npresent conditions of the Muslims in the\nPhilippines and their struggle for right to self-\ndetermination.'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_3', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_3', 'index': 3, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='1. To present a fair and objective history of\nthe Muslims and the Lumads in the\nPhilippines which are not mentioned in the\nManila-centered history books.\n 2. To understand the tenets and teachings of\nIslam.\n3. To illustrate the reasons, causes and effect\nof the Spanish Moro War\n4. To fully understand the rightful claim of the\nMuslims and the Lumads in the Philippines of\ntheir ancestral domain taken from them\nthrough a systematic and legal land grabbing.\n 5. To fully understand the just claim of the\nMuslims and the Lumads in the Philippines of\ntheir struggle for self-determination.\n 6. To present a comparative discussion and\nassessment on the different peace formulas\ninitiated by the Philippine Government in its\ndesire to solve the Mindanao problem\nThe course is a University/BOR mandated\ncourse. It is taken by the students both BS/BA\nand technology program. This subject is in\n\nUNOFFICIAL'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_4', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_4', 'index': 4, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='UNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cline with the mandate of the University to\npromote understanding and the culture of\npeace among the students of MSU, and in\ngeneral to the tri-people of MINSUPALA. To\nbe specific, the course outputs are the\nfollowing;\n\n1. Acquire working knowledge on the history,\nculture and way of life of the Muslims and the\nLumads of MINSUPALA such that they are\nable to discuss them competently.\n2. Share insights or views on issues pertaining\nto Mindanao and the Moro right to self-\ndetermination.\n3. Actively contribute in understanding and\nappreciating the history, culture and way of\nlife of the Muslim Filipinos and the Lumads.\n4. Demonstrate their concerns in the\ndevelopment of their community, people, and\nthe nation.\n 5. Able to critically and constructively react\nto current issues in Mindanao.\n6. Manifest respect and sympathy for other\npeoples in Mindanao coming from different\ncultural backgrounds;\n\nD. New Proposed Code Course\nHIS003\n\nGEC210\n\nUNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cResolution No. 131, S. 2023'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_5', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_5', 'index': 5, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='D. New Proposed Code Course\nHIS003\n\nGEC210\n\nUNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cResolution No. 131, S. 2023\n\nAnnex “F”\n\nPanukalang Kurso\n\nPetsa: Hunyo 29, 2023\nProponent: Mga Faculty ng Departamento ng Filipino at Iba Pang Wika, MSU System\n\nRationale\nA. Description of the Courses\n\nFilipino  101  (Wika  at  Kultura  sa\n\nMapayapang Lipunan)\n\nFilipino\n102\nPagpapahalaga sa Kalikasan)\n\n(Ekokritisismo\n\nat\n\nAng  kursong  ito  ay  naglalayong  magamit  ang\nwikang  Filipino  at  ibang  pangunahing  wika  sa\nMindanao sa pag-aaral ng mga kultura ng Rehiyong\nMINSUPALA tungo sa pagkakaisa at mapayapang\nlipunan.\n\nAng  kursong  ito  ay  nag-aanalisa  sa  mga  akdang\npampanitikang gaya ng tula at awit na nauugnay sa\nkalikasan,  kapaligiran  at  ekolohiya.  Hangarin  ng\nkursong  mapahalagahan  ang  ganda  ng  kapaligiran,\nng  kalikasan  at  makapagmungkahi  ng  mga\necofriendly na proyekto para sa kapakinabangan ng\npaaralan at komunidad.\n\nB. Expected Impact on Students'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_6', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_6', 'index': 6, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='B. Expected Impact on Students\n\nAng  mga  mag-aaral  ay  nakapagbabahagi  ng\nkanilang karanasan sa kanilang mga kaklase upang\nmapanatili\nat\nnaipagmamalaki  ang  nakasanayang  kultura.  Ito  ay\nnatatamo sa kursong Filipino 101.\n\npakikipagkapwa-tao\n\nang\n\nAng mga mag-aaral ay nakapagsusuri ng mga krisis\nukol  sa  ekolohiya  sa  pamamagitan  ng  ugnayan  ng\npanitikan,  kultura  at  kapaligirang  pisikal.  Ang\nkursong Filipino 102 ay isang kamalayan sa tunay na\nkalagayan  ng  ekolohiya  sa  kasalukuyang  panahon,\ndahil dito ang isang mag-aaral ay dapat na makapag-\nambag  ng  mayamang  kaisipan  para  sa  Inang\nKalikasan.\n\nUNOFFICIAL'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_7', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_7', 'index': 7, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='UNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cC. Evaluation and Output of the Courses  Nasa ikaapat na taon na ang dalawang kursong ito sa\nkurikula  ng  mga  programa  ng  mga  kolehiyo  sa\nMindanao  State  University,  napatunayan  ng  mga\nguro ng Departamento ng  Filipino, na ang  Filipino\n101 at Filipino 102 ay dalawang mahalagang kurso\nna  hindi  dapat  tanggalin  sa  kurikula,  ito  ay  upang\nmapanatili  sa  mga  mag-aaral  ang  magandang\npakikitungo sa kapwa lalo pa’t ang MSU ay binubuo\nng kultural na dibersidad; at ang pagpapahalaga sa\nkalikasan  at  kapaligiran  ay\nsa\nkapaligirang\nkamalayan\nng\npagdebelop\nkinabibilangan  ng  mga  mag-aaral,  at  upang\nmaunawaan  kung  paanong  ang  sosyal,  natural  at\npisikal na kapaligiran ay nakakaapekto sa kalusugan\nat kabutihan ng isang komunidad.\n*nasa kabilang pahina ang output ng mga magaaral\n\ntumutulong\n\nsa\n\nD. New Proposed Code Course\n\nFilipino 101\n\nFilipino 102\n\nGEC 120\nGEC 130\n\nUNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cCourse Proposal'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_8', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_8', 'index': 8, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='tumutulong\n\nsa\n\nD. New Proposed Code Course\n\nFilipino 101\n\nFilipino 102\n\nGEC 120\nGEC 130\n\nUNOFFICIAL\n\n\x0cCourse Proposal\n\nDate: June 29,, 2023\nProponent: Faculty of the Department of Filipino and Other Languages, MSU System\n\nRationale\nA. Description of the Courses\n\nFilipino  101  (Wika  at  Kultura  sa\n\nMapayapang Lipunan)\n\n102\nFilipino\nPagpapahalaga sa Kalikasan)\n\n(Ekokritisismo\n\nat\n\nE. Expected Impact on Students\n\nThis  course  aims  to  use  the  Filipino  language  and\nother languages use in Mindanao in the study of the\ncultures of the MINSUPALA Region towards unity\nand a peaceful society.\n\nThis course analyzes literary  works such as poetry\nand song related to nature, environment and ecology.\nThe  course  aims  to  appreciate  the  beauty  of  the\nenvironment,  nature  and  propose  ecofriendly\nprojects for the benefit of the school and community.'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_9', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_9', 'index': 9, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='Students  are  able  to  share  their  experiences  with\ntheir  classmates  to  maintain  social  interaction  and\nshowcase their culture and native language. This is\nachieved in the Filipino 101 course.\n\nStudents are able to analyze ecological crisis through\nthe intersection of literature, culture and the physical\nenvironment.  The  Filipino  102  course  develops  an\nenvironmental and ecological awareness, because of\nthis  the  student  should  be  able  to  contribute  rich\nthinking to help save mother earth.\n\nUNOFFICIAL\x0cF. Evaluation and Output of the Courses'), Document(id='doc_69_chunk_10', metadata={'id': 'doc_69_chunk_10', 'index': 10, 'doc_id': 69}, page_content='UNOFFICIAL\x0cF. Evaluation and Output of the Courses\n\nThese two courses are now in their fourth year in the\ncurricula  of  the  colleges,  the  faculty  of  the\nDepartment  of  Filipino  have  proven  that  Filipino\n101 and Filipino 102 are two important core courses\nthat should not be excluded in the curricula for the\nstudents to maintain good relations with others since\nMSU has a cultural diversity; and by valuing nature\nand the environment helps develop awareness of the\nenvironment\nto\nin  which  students\nunderstand  how  the  social,  natural  and  physical\nenvironment  affect  the  health  and  well-being  of  a\ncommunity.\n*students output on the other page\n\nlive,  and\n\nG. New Proposed Code Course\n\nFilipino 101\n\nFilipino 102\n\nGEC 120\nGEC 130\n\nUNOFFICIAL')]
