INFO 2025-04-21 07:19:38,724 documents 449 139646331721408 Chunks: [Document(id='doc_71_chunk_0', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_0', 'index': 0, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='Office of the Chancellor\n\nJ-S-\n\nchancellor@g.msuiit.edu.ph\n\nSeptember 8, 2022\n\nMEMORANDUM\n\nTO:\n\nAll Responsibility Center Heads\nAll Financial Analysts and Assistants\nThis University\n\nSUBJECT:\n\nDeadline for Submission of Approved Project Procurement\nManagement Plan (PPMP) for FY 2023\n\nAll Responsibility Centers (RCs) are to submit their respective approved Project\nProcurement Management Plans (PPMPs) FY 2023 for GAA (Fund 01), Income (Fund 05), and\nFiduciary (Fund 05) to the Procurement Management Division (PMD) on or before October 14,\n2022 for consolidation into the Annual Procurement Plan (APP). PPMPs submitted late will not\nbe included in the APP.\n\nPPMPs shall strictly conform to the following:\n\n•  PPMPs shall be generated by accessing the online form, saved in the system and\n\nprinted;'), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_1', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_1', 'index': 1, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='PPMPs shall strictly conform to the following:\n\n•  PPMPs shall be generated by accessing the online form, saved in the system and\n\nprinted;\n\n•  Use of proper account code for each item shall be observed;\n•  PPMP shall be based on the work plan of the RC’s;\n•  The printed copy shall be processed through the Office of the Budget Management to\nensure consistency with the RCs submitted financial plan, compliance with budget rules\nand regulations, appropriateness of funding charge/proper account, and approval by the\nconcerned head of the cluster, prior to submission to the BAG Secretariat;\n\n•  Separate PPMPs shall be generated for each source of fund;\n•  Specifications for the procurement of goods shall be based on relevant characteristics\n\nand/or performance requirement; reference to brand names shall not be allowed;'), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_2', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_2', 'index': 2, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='and/or performance requirement; reference to brand names shall not be allowed;\n\n•  PPMPs for infrastructure projects, repairs, renovations, and consultations shall indicate\nthe general description, scope, and parameters. However, the approved detailed\nprogram of works, engineering plans, and others shall be submitted the soonest time\npossible to the PMD;\n\n•  PPMPs must be judiciously and meticulously prepared considering that actual\n\nprocurement or implementation shall be done in the succeeding fiscal year;\n\n•  Unforeseen contingencies shall have budget considerations;\n•  RCs with several departments should submit a consolidated PPMP. Breaking down of\n\nitems shall be internal to the concerned RC;\n\n•'), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_3', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_3', 'index': 3, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='•  Unforeseen contingencies shall have budget considerations;\n•  RCs with several departments should submit a consolidated PPMP. Breaking down of\n\nitems shall be internal to the concerned RC;\n\n•\n\n•  On-line submission (saving in the FMIS) shall not warrant the PPMP of the\nResponsibility Center to be included in the consolidated APP, unless the PPMP is also\nprinted and approved by the concerned head of cluster and submitted to PMD;\nIn compliance with the requirement of the COA, all PPMPs (non-generic) shall be\nattached with approved purchase or job order request and Approved Budget of the\nContract (ABC), except for the Office Supplies and Other Supplies and Materials\nExpenses. The form for the ABC is available at the “Faculty and Staff Downloads” in our\nwebsite; and'), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_4', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_4', 'index': 4, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content="•  The account codes shall not be in generic form, otherwise the PPMP shall not be\naccepted by the PMD, unless a justification letter signed by the RC Head is attached.\nBelow are the proper account codes and their description:\n\nmsuiit\n\nInfluencing the Future\n\nILIGAN ADDRESS\nAndres Bonifacio'i Avenue, Tibanga, lligan City, Philippines\nTelefax (063)221-4056(01)\n(063) 221-4050 to 55 (TL)\n\nMANILA ADDRESS\nMSU-IIT LIAISON OFFICE (MILO)\n12th Floor G.E. Antonio Building\nT.M Kalaw Avenue Cor. J. Bocobo, St Ermita, Manila\nTel 527-5595\n\n\x0cOffice of the Chancellor\n\nchancellor@g. msuiit.edu.ph\n\nAccount Code\n\nDescription\n\n5020399000-002\n\nCooking Gas Expenses\n\n5060405007-001\n\nCommunication Equipment\n\n5060602001-001\n\nComputer Software\n\n5060405009-001\n\nDisaster Response and Rescue Equipment - FireFighting\n\n5060407001-001\n\nFurniture and Fixtures\n\n5060405003-001\n\nInformation and Communication Technology Equipment\n\n5020308000-003\n\nLaboratory Supplies Expense-Academic\n\n5020308000-001"), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_5', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_5', 'index': 5, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='5060407001-001\n\nFurniture and Fixtures\n\n5060405003-001\n\nInformation and Communication Technology Equipment\n\n5020308000-003\n\nLaboratory Supplies Expense-Academic\n\n5020308000-001\n\nMedical, Dental, Lab Supplies\n\n5020308000-002\n\nMedical, Dental, Lab Supplies (CLINIC)\n\n5060405011-001\n\nMedical Equipment\n\n5020301000-001\n\nOffice Supplies Expenses\n\n5060405002-001\n\nOffice Equipment\n\n5060405099-001\n\nOther Machinery and Equipment\n\n5060409099-001\n\nOther Property, Plant and Equipment\n\n5020399000-001\n\nOther Supplies and Materials Expenses\n\n5060405012-001\n\nPrinting Equipment\n\n5020322002-001\n\nSemi-Expendables Books Expenses\n\n5020321007-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Communication Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321008-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Disaster Response and Rescue Equipment\n\n5020322001-001 Semi-Expendable Furniture and Fixtures Expenses\n\n5020321003-001\n\nSemi-Expendable ICT Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321002-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Office Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321099-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Other Machinery and Equipment'), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_6', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_6', 'index': 6, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='5020321003-001\n\nSemi-Expendable ICT Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321002-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Office Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321099-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Other Machinery and Equipment\n\n5020321011-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Printing Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321012-001\n\nSemi_-Expendable Sports Equipment Expenses\n\n5020321013-001\n\nSemi-Expendable Technical and Scientific Equipment\n\n5060405013-001 Sports Equipment\n\n5060405014-001\n\nTechnical and Scientific Equipment\n\nmsuiit\n\nInfluencing the Future\n\nILIGAN ADDRESS\nAndres Bonifacio . Avenue. Tibanga. Iligan City. Philippines\nTelefax: (063) 221-4056 (DL)\n(063) 221-4050 to 55 (TL)\n\nMANILA ADDRESS\nMSU-IIT LIAISON OFFICE (MILO)\n12th Floor G.E. Antonio Building\nTM. Kalaw Avenue Cor J. Bocobo, St. Ermlta, Manila\nTel 527-5595\n\n\x0cOffice of the Chancellor\n\nAa\n\nchancellor@g.msuiit.edu.ph'), Document(id='doc_71_chunk_7', metadata={'id': 'doc_71_chunk_7', 'index': 7, 'doc_id': 71}, page_content='Office of the Chancellor\n\nAa\n\nchancellor@g.msuiit.edu.ph\n\nThe Financial Analysts are also reminded of Section 7.2 of the Revised Implementing\nRules and Regulations (IRR) of RA 9184, which states that "No procurement shall be\nundertaken unless it is in accordance with the approved APR of the procuring entity.” Therefore,\nsupplemental PPMPs shall be consolidated into APP and be processed only when there is\nsupplemental budget, otherwise, previously approved and submitted PPMP will be revised.\n\nFor strict compliance.\n\nALIZB\n/ Ghana\n\nM. DITUCALAN\n\nmsuiit\n\nInfluencing the Future\n\nILIGAN ADDRESS\nAndres Bonifacio i Avenue, Tibanga, lligan City. Philippines\nTelefax (063)221-4056 (DL)\n(063) 221-4050 to 55 (TL)\n\nMANILA ADDRESS\nMSU-IIT LIAISON OFFICE (MILO)\n12th Floor G.E. Antonio Building\nT.M Kalaw Avenue Cor J Bocobo, St Ermita, Manila\nTel 527-5595')]
